Larry writes the number 3 on his pinky finger.  He then applies $f$ to 3 and writes the output on his ring finger.  If Larry continues this process of applying $f$ and writing the output on a new finger, what number will Larry write on his tenth finger?

Let $P$ be a point inside triangle $ABC$.  Let $G_1$, $G_2$, and $G_3$ be the centroids of triangles $PBC$, $PCA$, and $PAB$, respectively.  If the area of triangle $ABC$ is 18, then find the area of triangle $G_1 G_2 G_3$.

[asy]
import geometry;

unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, P;
pair[] G;

A = (1,3);
B = (0,0);
C = (4,0);
P = (2,1);
G[1] = (P + B + C)/3;
G[2] = (P + C + A)/3;
G[3] = (P + A + B)/3;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--P);
draw(B--P);
draw(C--P);
draw(G[1]--G[2]--G[3]--cycle);

label("$A$", A, dir(90));
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
dot("$G_1$", G[1], S);
dot("$G_2$", G[2], SE);
dot("$G_3$", G[3], NW);
label("$P$", P, S);
[/asy]

If \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
x^2-4 &\quad \text{if } x \ge -4, \\
x + 3 &\quad \text{otherwise},
\end{cases}
\]then for how many values of $x$ is $f(f(x)) = 5$?

Let $f$ be defined by  \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
2-x & \text{ if } x \leq 1, \\
2x-x^2 & \text{ if } x>1.
\end{array}
\right.\]Calculate $f^{-1}(-3)+f^{-1}(0)+f^{-1}(3)$.

Two of the altitudes of an acute triangle divide the sides into segments of lengths $5,3,2$ and $x$ units, as shown. What is the value of $x$? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7)); size(75);
pair A = (0,0);
pair B = (1,0);
pair C = (74/136,119/136);
pair D = foot(B, A, C);
pair E = /*foot(A,B,C)*/ (52*B+(119-52)*C)/(119);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--D);
draw(A--E);
draw(rightanglemark(A,D,B,1.2));
draw(rightanglemark(A,E,B,1.2));
label("$3$",(C+D)/2,WNW+(0,0.3));
label("$5$",(A+D)/2,NW);
label("$2$",(C+E)/2,E);
label("$x$",(B+E)/2,NE);
[/asy]

